    <id>https://www.nber.org/papers/w35461</id>
    <title>Should We Tax Trade? A Pigouvian Perspective</title>
    <updated>2026-07-01T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Arnaud Costinot &amp; Iván Werning</name>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;b&gt; NBER Working Papers&lt;/b&gt; &lt;br&gt;We develop a simple and intuitive Pigouvian perspective on optimal trade policy. Our approach  unifies a wide range of rationales for taxing trade, from the classical optimal tariff argument to contemporary debates about global carbon emissions and geopolitics. We also clarify when trade policy intervention is warranted and when alternative domestic instruments should be used instead.</content>
